params.name: o

Object that contains all paramters from wiki

}

name: src/region.js
constructor
description:
The init function creates a new region object to keep track of region specific information
like location, template name, region name, etc.

params.name: region_name
params.description: Name of the region you want to control

params.name: template_name
params.description: Name of the containing template

params.name: origin_xy
params.description: Array of the regions' starting top left coordinates, [x,y]

params.name: origin_size
params.description: Array of the regions' size [x,y]

name: Seek
description: Seeks to the next content item in that region

unknown.tagValue: {String} regionName Name of the region you want to seek

params.name: direction
params.description: Direction of pagination prev|next|first

params.name: wrap
params.description: Controls what happens when reach the end of the list

name: moveTo
description: The move function moves a region to a new set of xy coordinantes using predefined easing types.

params.name: end_pos
params.description: A list of [x,y] cordinates for the end position of the top left of the region

params.name: duration
params.description: How long the animation lasts in milliseconds

params.name: type
params.description: What kind of easing to apply to the tween animation

name: resize
description: The resize function resises a region to a new set of xy coordinantes using predefined easing types.

params.name: end_size
params.description: A list of [x,y] cordinates for the end size

params.name: duration
params.description: How long the animation lasts in milliseconds

params.name: type
params.description: What kind of easing to apply to the tween animation

name: _animateRegionInit
description: Intializes some variables for use in the animation and calls the main animation method

params.name: end_coords
params.description: [x,y] list of the end coordinates you want the region to move to

params.name: duration
params.description: How long the animation plays in milliseconds

params.name: type
params.description: The easting type used for the tweening animation

name: _animateRegion
description: Main animation loop, computes the next [x,y] values of the animation

params.name: end_coords
params.description: [x,y] list of the end coordinates you want the region to move to

params.name: cX
params.description: The total delta of the X coordinate from beginning position to end position

params.name: cY
params.description: The total delta of theY coordinate from beginning position to end position

params.name: start_time
params.description: A datetime time object

params.name: end_time
params.description: A int or daytime object that represents the end of the animation

params.name: d
params.description: The duration of the animation in milliseconds

params.name: type
params.description: The easting type used for the tweening animation

description:
Restarts the template, be careful!  If you don't have a span region
set this will spawn a new process.
